IN THE UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF GENEVIVE WILDS FOR A WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS} No.39895 ORDER

This mattercoming on regularly for hearing and it appearing to the court that proceedings have been commenced in the Juvenile court in relation to the matters herein involved and that the best interests of all parties concerned that the matter be heard in the Juvenile court, now therfore, upon motion of the attorney for petitioner, this proceeding in this court is hereby dismissed withought prejudice.
Done in open court this 26th day of Febuary, 1918
IN THE UNITED STATED DISTRICT COURT FOR THE WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON,NORTHERN DIV.
IN THE MATTER OF THE APPLICATION OF GUNEVIVE WILDS FOR W WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.
FILED IN THE U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington NORTHERN DIVISION FEB26 1918 FRANK L.CROSBY CLERK EDIN FAXW
